`IFormFile` buffers into memory by default — for large files, you need to **disable form buffering** and read the multipart stream manually.

### Key changes

**1. Disable the request size limit and form buffering:**

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    // read the multipart boundary from Content-Type
    var boundary = request.GetMultipartBoundary()
        ?? throw new BadHttpRequestException("Missing multipart boundary");

    var reader = new MultipartReader(boundary, request.Body);
    var section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync();

    while (section is not null)
    {
        if (ContentDispositionHeaderValue.TryParse(
                section.ContentDisposition, out var cd) && cd.IsFileDisposition())
        {
            var destPath = Path.Combine("/tmp/uploads",
                Path.GetRandomFileName());

            await using var fs = File.Create(destPath);
            await section.Body.CopyToAsync(fs);   // streams chunk-by-chunk
        }
        section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync();
    }

    return Results.Ok("Uploaded");
})
.DisableAntiforgery()
.WithRequestTimeout(TimeSpan.FromMinutes(30));
```

**2. Raise Kestrel's limits in `Program.cs`:**

```csharp
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(k =>
{
    k.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024; // 2 GB
});

// also raise the form options default (even though you bypass it)
builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(o =>
{
    o.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024;
});
```

### Why this works

| Approach | Memory used for a 2 GB file |
|---|---|
| `IFormFile` | ~2 GB (full buffer) |
| `MultipartReader` | ~80 KB (streaming) |

`MultipartReader` reads the raw request body section-by-section and `CopyToAsync` flushes to disk in small chunks (default 80 KB), so memory stays flat regardless of file size.

### Gotchas

- **Reverse proxy limits** — if behind Nginx/IIS, raise `client_max_body_size` / `maxAllowedContentLength` there too.
- **No model binding** — you lose `[FromForm]`; parse non-file fields from `section.AsFormDataSection()`.
- **Timeouts** — the default 30 s request timeout will kill large uploads; extend it as shown above.
